About this hotel

This elegant, Moorish-style hotel is 5 km from Koutoubia Mosque and 6 km from the bustling public square of Jemaa el-Fnaa.

Check-in time: 2:00 PM
Check-out time: 12:00 PM

    Claire Mills2 months ago on Google
    3/5
    Would be easy to only moan about the negatives but will be fair and balanced. Firstly the staff are lovely, kind and friendly. The food is outstanding and always fresh and delicious. It was 5 star and consistent. There was a lot of variety 
    Would be easy to only moan about the negatives but will be fair and balanced. Firstly the staff are lovely, kind and friendly. The food is outstanding and always fresh and delicious. It was 5 star and consistent. There was a lot of variety and the chefs were amazing. The rooms were spacious and cleaned daily. Attention to detail was good in that cleaners added nice touches and replenished soaps and clean towels etc. But the fabric of the building needs checking - hairdryer didnt work and shower door hinge was broken (neither were able to be fixed during our stay). Air con wasnt effective but, to be fair, they send a service team to fix it straight away. The unfortunate result being that they asked my son to stay in the room for several ours as the outside agency that came to fix it werent allowed to be in the room alone (would have been more of a 5 star hotel experience if someone from the hotel could have overseen this rather than expecting the holiday maker to sit waiting in.). The negative for us was the music. Fine to have a bar with live music and fine to have music for aqua gym etc etc. But seriously, it was pumped out of two huge speakers all day by the pool and well into the night in the reception area. We couldnt snooze by the pool or read our books and couldnt chat in the cool reception lounging area in the evening. Sure, some wanted to dance and thats nice but there was nowhere to get away from it if you didnt want that vibe. The strapline of the hotel, on their website, is A Haven of Peace. Its not that. They are more 18/30s trying to be Ibiza trendy. There arent enough sunloungers for everyone and nowhere near enough umbrellas so everyone ends up securing them as early as possible and then watching as others arrive and have nowhere to sit or have no shade. Towels are cleaned daily but arrive mid morning so theres a long wait and then a scrabble to get them. Its not fair on the pool staff who are lovely and trying to do their best but simply dont have the resources to do their jobs effectively. Its not their fault but the experience isnt 5 star at all and I felt sorry for them as people were getting frustrated daily. There werent enough people staffing the pool bar so there was a long wait and the place was crawling with wasps - staff getting stung often. The poolside snacks were all pastries so nothing for anyone needing a gluten free option. All in all we had a good time - the concierge Sharief was wonderful and arranged some fabulous outings for us and would have moved mountains for our comfort. Some attention to the fabric of the hotel and a rethink of the entertainment (separate areas to suit both those who want and those who dont want thumping base all day long) would make this a better hotel. Go for the food though and the experience of being in Marrakech - the people are special and the city is incredible.

    Great clean hotel with a big pool, great extensive breakfast and friendly staff.

    Room 261 nice view of pool, very comfortable bed with plenty storage did have to ask for hangers to hang clothes in wardrobe. No iron available at hotel so we brought one from Carrefour supermarket for around 5.00.
    Pool is great very friendly staff around with plenty of beds loungers even at peak times there is availability all day. Please note this is a family hotel so expect loads children around the pool etc. maybe more during the school holidays.
    Breakfast was great huge choice! Great fresh omelette station, fresh pancakes, loads pastries, cooked dishes, juices etc.
    Hotel location its 15 mins from airport by taxi. 15-20 mins from city centre approx. Hotel is safe secure with private entrance. There is a large carrefour supermarket on lower level at Al azar mall 5-10 min walk from hotel. Walk down to hotel entrance by barrier turn right walk along perimeter then turn right walk along into car park and across the road is Al azar mall. The supermarket there has everything including well stocked alcohol area.
    There is a free shuttle bud the hotel runs to the medina square few times a day get times from reception.
    Over all il give it five stars just little things need to be addressed. Like a welcome drink for guests, have some irons available for guests. The staff are all very friendly, the hotel is clean and very comfortable beds.

Not a major issue but somewhat spoils the surprise!

This is sold as a 4-5 star hotel and they are running out of towels on a daily basis. The management are aware of this from previous feedback. All the staff are aware this is a daily problem. Simple fixbuy another 100 towels!

    o When I commented and asked if there was any hot vegetables I was pointed to a microwave.the first 4-5 star hotel where Ive had to reheat my own food!

    I can highly recommend the Menara Palace, especially if youre looking for a relaxing break which doesnt come with the noise and bustle of the city centre. Pulling up at the entrance, even relatively late in the evening, everything was naturally taken care of and the friendly reception desk completed proceedings quickly.
    I had the delight of being allocated a top third floor room with a pool view. The interior of all the corridors is a minimalistic style but very pretty, broken up with open air plantation sections.
    The room was very impressive and I certainly recommend paying the slight extra for a pool view. It was so spacious, complete with sofa and arm chain, desk, massive bed and lots of storage space along with wardrobe, in a separate section of the room. Lots of lighting options which could be controlled from the bed, along with electric sockets at both sides of the bed added to the comfort levels. There were tea and coffee facilities as well as a mini bar. The huge french doors and window opened up to a spacious balcony with table and chairs. Outdoor lights made this space useable late at night too. The thick curtains were very effective at blocking out the light in the mornings.
    The bathroom was equally as spacious as the main room, with two sinks, a separate large bath and shower cubicle as well as a toilet and bidet in another room. Towels and gowns were present although I couldnt find any slippers. The toiletries came in small bottles but were kept restocked well and the shower had decent power as well as getting hot quickly. What was a shame was that there was no guide to the hotel facilities within the room. An overview of the dining options, how the pool worked, entertainment in the evening etc was all missing which resulting in making the most of my stay harder. The TV was also rather difficult to use and temperamental, requiring a channel change to restore a frozen picture regularly. Most frustrating though was the wifi which didnt work very well at all. The rest of the hotel wasnt as bad, so I assume the room was maybe on the edges of the signal.
    Theres a lot of range in the breakfast buffet - traditional meats and fruits, hot dishes, pastries and a range of fruit juices were all present. Theres also a counter with freshly made sweet items should you need a morning sugar fix. No dishes made to order were available which I could see and hot drinks are also self service. Theres plenty of seating both inside and outside which is nice and the staff were good at clearing plates etc. Service ends promptly at 10:30.
    The main selling point for this hotel is its outdoor pool.Theres actually two pools with a smaller one which is heated in the cooler months. Theres loads of sun loungers around the pool, a decent number of cabanas for at least two people as well as beanbags on the grass and a number of tables surrounding. Towels are provided from a hut alongside the DJ which plays non obtrusive music in the afternoon. The huge pool has steps down at the top and a shallow section at the opposite end, next to the restaurant / bar. Its a shame they dont offer service to the sun beds and, to be honest, the service from the bar itself is a little slow, but overall everyone was friendly and the food available is good for lunch with reasonable prices. It was all served quickly and presented well.
    Theres three main restaurants in the hotel and I had the pleasure of trying two for dinner during my visit. The first, specialising in Italian food, was pretty quite on the Tuesday evening but the staff were friendly and the food served in good time. The Moroccan restaurant the following night was much better! An authentic setting with low sofas and live traditional ude music gave a fantastic experience. There was a good range on the menu and my starter, although not as I expected, was delicious and filling in itself. The traditional tagine main was one of a few options but didnt disappoint. A really enjoyable evening and a meal.

    james poole-cowley3 years ago on Google
    5/5
    A delightful hotel. Large site with the building a "horseshoe square" around two outside pools and gardens. Clever gardening sections off areas of seating so that it doesn't feel too much like a line of sun loungers. 
    A delightful hotel. Large site with the building a "horseshoe square" around two outside pools and gardens. Clever gardening sections off areas of seating so that it doesn't feel too much like a line of sun loungers.
    I stayed over winter and although cool in the morning and evenings the weather is more than sufficient to swim in the smaller pool during the day.
    Food was good very good in the buffet and I was pleasantly surprised given to ocassion critical review of it.
    The devour is a little tired in sections. This doesn't trouble me as nothing is "new" once opened to the public but I suspect is the route of some of the negative comments along the lines of "this is not a 5 star establishment"
    The SPA and indoor pool section is a franchise and as such comes with significant surplus charge. I have therefore not used these and can't comment on their quality. The pool does come in at 15-20 which is of course very steep.
    The staff have been nothing but delightful and helpful. All I have encountered speak perfect English, and French substantially better than me.
    There is a shuttle bus that takes you into town. It drops you off approximately 10 mins from Jemaa El Fna, a rather pleasant stroll through Parc Lalla Hasna and across a main road. They run 10, 12, 15, 19 and return 15 mins later. For an included service I found this more than sufficient but if you are mobility issues you will of course need to invest in private taxis at a cost of between 50 to 70 Diram.
    Overall relaxing, enhanced my experience, convenient to explore the hussel and bussel but pleasant estate to retreat back to. There is some noise outside from a road and ocassion aircraft as the airport is so near the city and thus hotel is the west side also.

    Mechouar-Kasbah

    Expansive Mechouar-Kasbah takes in part of the walled old town, plus the sprawling ruins of 16th-century El Badii Palace, and the Saadian Tombs mausoleum, with ornate pillars, tiles, and stucco. The Mellah, or Jewish quarter, is home to the restored Slat Al Azama Synagogue, said to date to 1492. Outside the walls, the extensive Agdal Gardens were laid out in the 12th century with citrus orchards and a vast pool.

    About this hotel

    This elegant, Moorish-style hotel is 5 km from Koutoubia Mosque and 6 km from the bustling public square of Jemaa el-Fnaa.

    The polished rooms and suites feature balconies and sitting areas, plus free Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs, minibars and coffeemakers. Suites add separate living rooms; some have fireplaces.

    Freebies include breakfast served in a buffet-style restaurant. Other eateries include a cozy restaurant with alcoves and a fireplace, a rooftop bar/lounge with tapas, cocktails and mountain views, and a poolside bar with snacks. There's also a spa, a fitness room, and indoor and outdoor pools. Parking is available.
